## Data — LSJ Lexicon & Morphology (Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0)

The LSJ lexicon data and Morpheus morphology databases (`data/lsj.db`,
`data/morph.db`) are licensed under:

**Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International**
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

**Attribution:** Chicago Digital Classics, Liddell–Scott–Jones Lexicon, via the Perseus Digital Library project.

## Data — English-Icelandic Bridge Glossary (Creative Commons Attribution 4.0)

The bridge glossary (`data/IS-EN_glossary.tsv`) used to translate LSJ's
English glosses into Icelandic is licensed under:

**Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International**
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

**Attribution:** English-Icelandic/Icelandic-English glossary 21.09, The
Árni Magnússon Institute for Icelandic Studies / Reykjavik University, via
CLARIN Iceland. See CREDITS.md for full author list.

## Data — Wiktionary Supplement (Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0)

The supplementary EN->IS pairs (`data/wiktionary_en_is.tsv`), extracted
from English Wiktionary via kaikki.org/wiktextract, are licensed under:

**Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International** (dual with GFDL)
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

**Attribution:** English Wiktionary contributors, via kaikki.org
(wiktextract by Tatu Ylonen). See CREDITS.md for full citation.

## Data — Icelandic Morphology / BÍN (Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0)

The extracted Icelandic declension/verb-form data
(`data/is_noun_declension.tsv`, `data/is_verb_forms.tsv`), sourced from
BÍN (Beygingarlýsing íslensks nútímamáls / DMII), is licensed under:

**Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International**
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

**Attribution:** Kristín Bjarnadóttir, The Árni Magnússon Institute for
Icelandic Studies, via CLARIN Iceland. See CREDITS.md for full citation.

## Data — Generated Icelandic Glosses (Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0)

The Icelandic bridge glosses this project generates (`data/lsj_is.db`, and
the Icelandic text baked into any compiled `.dictionary` bundle) are a
derivative of the CC BY-SA-licensed LSJ text, so ShareAlike propagates:
**this project's own license grant for the generated Icelandic data is
CC BY-SA 4.0.**

**You are free to:**
- Share — copy and redistribute the material
- Adapt — remix, transform, and build upon the material

**Under the following terms:**
- Attribution — give appropriate credit to all sources listed above
- ShareAlike — distribute your contributions under the same license

---

## Summary

When distributing this dictionary:
1. Include/reference all licenses above
2. Attribute the Chicago LSJ source, the CLARIN bridge glossary, the
   Wiktionary supplement, and the BÍN morphology data (see CREDITS.md)
3. Any derivative works using the generated Icelandic glosses or
   morphology data must also be CC BY-SA 4.0

